x4freetext: Lu-100 at the Institute For High Energy
Targets were made of metal or salt powders. The
metallic foils of known thickness 0.2-0.5 mm were used
to cut out discs 10 or 15 mm in diameter, the powders
were pressed into tablets 0.4-0.7 g/cm**2, 15. or
20 mm in diameter. The tablets were wrapped up in Al
foil, 10 mum, the KBr and NaI tablets had an additional
thin air-tight polyethylene shell to avoid losses of
radioactive krypton and xenon during irradiation.

x4freetext: Standard deviation from the mean value
.The systematic error was estimated to be
+-20%, it mainly resulted from the errors in the
detector efficiency and proton intensity measurements.
